BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:568@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260605
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260606
SUMMARY:BWA: Parent/Carer Coffee Morning -  Supporting Your Child with BIG Emotions
DESCRIPTION:The Education Wellbeing Service hosts a coffee morning at BWA to discuss managing big emotions in children.\n\nThe Education Wellbeing Service will be hosting a coffee morning at BWA. The main focus will be supporting your child to manage big emotions, understanding emotion regulation, and learning practical strategies. Provided by Battersea Education Wellbeing Service.
CATEGORIES:WELLBEING
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:570@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:BWA: Parents Morning
DESCRIPTION:Parents are invited to a welcome reception and classroom activities.\n\nParents are invited to a welcome reception from 8:50am to 9:10am, followed by classroom activities from 9:15am to 10:00am. Only one parent per child is permitted. Note: CM2B/Y6B session is postponed to the final French focus week.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:633@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260623
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260624
SUMMARY:BWA: Heatwave Safety Measures
DESCRIPTION:School remains open during the heatwave. Please ensure children have water bottles, sun hats, and sunscreen.\n\nSchool remains open as normal during the heatwave. Parents are asked to ensure children arrive with at least one, ideally two, named water bottles (frozen recommended), wear a sun hat, have sunscreen applied before school, and wear appropriate lightweight summer uniform. Coats, jumpers, cardigans, and fleeces should not be worn unless there is a specific medical reason.
CATEGORIES:WELLBEING
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:634@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:BWA: Tesco Stronger Starts Voting Deadline
DESCRIPTION:Deadline to vote for the BWA PTA Healthy Food Project at participating Tesco stores using blue tokens.\n\nThe BWA PTA’s Healthy Food Project has been shortlisted for the Tesco Stronger Starts community grant. Voting is open until 31 July 2026. Please shop at participating Tesco stores, receive a blue token, and place it in the BWA PTA slot to support the school's healthy eating and wellbeing hub project.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
